<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Daisy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Daisy,</orth> the plant Bellis perennis: <cit><quote>whose perfect white showed like an April d. on the grass,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 395" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 395</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ies pied,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.904" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 904</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there's a d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.184" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 184</bibl></cit> (of what significance?). <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.170" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 170</bibl>.
